## Who Wrote This Review — And Why It's Different

I'm [Farzana Hasan](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/), a GIA Expert and Lead Critic at Diamond Critics. Every week I receive messages from readers who have already clicked "Place Order" on a Blue Nile ring — and are panicking because they just realized they bought a stone with a 63.5% depth, a crushed-ice table, and a mystery inclusion dead-center under the table facet that nobody at Blue Nile flagged.

This review exists to prevent exactly that.

For this audit I reviewed over 200 individual engagement ring listings — loose diamonds and settings — across every major carat tier from 0.5ct to 3ct, every primary setting style Blue Nile sells, and both natural and lab-grown diamonds. Every price in this article is linked to a real stone on Blue Nile's live inventory. Stone IDs are included so you can verify the price yourself before buying.

This article is the engagement ring hub inside the broader [Blue Nile Review](https://diamondcritics.com/blue-nile-review/) — my full ongoing audit of everything Blue Nile sells. I have separately reviewed [Blue Nile lab grown diamond rings](https://diamondcritics.com/blue-nile-lab-grown-diamond-rings-review/), [Blue Nile earrings](https://diamondcritics.com/blue-nile-earrings-review/), [Blue Nile bracelets](https://diamondcritics.com/blue-nile-bracelets-review/), [Blue Nile men's rings](https://diamondcritics.com/blue-nile-mens-rings-review/), [Blue Nile men's bracelets](https://diamondcritics.com/blue-nile-mens-bracelets-review/), and [Blue Nile men's chains](https://diamondcritics.com/blue-nile-mens-chains-review/).

