## 2 Carat Natural Engagement Ring Price Audit — Blue Nile 2026

At 2ct, the price environment changes completely. A GIA Excellent 1ct G-VS2 costs $3,230. The identical grade profile at 2ct costs $16,490 — a 410% increase for a face-up diameter increase of just 1.6mm (from 6.5mm to 8.1mm). This premium is real: only 2–3% of all mined rough yields a polished 2ct stone. Rarity is baked into every listing. This is what I call **The 2ct Commitment**.

<table class="dc-custom-table"><thead><tr><th>Grade</th><th>Blue Nile ID</th><th>Price</th><th>Setting Total*</th><th>Farzana's Verdict</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29307739?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">G-VS2 Excellent</a></strong></td><td>29307739</td><td>$16,490</td><td>~$17,190</td><td><strong>The 2ct floor. Correct choice for 93% of buyers. Stop here.</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29142126?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">F-VS2 Excellent</a></strong></td><td>29142126</td><td>$18,140</td><td>~$18,840</td><td>$1,650 over G-VS2 for one color step. Imperceptible in white gold.</td></tr><tr><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29308461?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">E-VVS2 Excellent</a></strong></td><td>29308461</td><td>$22,460</td><td>~$23,160</td><td>$5,970 over floor for two color grades + clarity jump. Hard to justify.</td></tr><tr><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29249620?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">G-VS1 Excellent</a></strong></td><td>29249620</td><td>$22,460</td><td>~$23,160</td><td>VS1 over VS2 at 2ct — $5,970 for a loupe-only distinction. Skip.</td></tr><tr><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28720470?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">D-VS2 Excellent</a></strong></td><td>28720470</td><td>$26,490</td><td>~$27,190</td><td>$10,000 colorless premium. Imperceptible to guests at 8.1mm in real lighting.</td></tr><tr><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26246337?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">D-VVS1 Excellent</a></strong></td><td>26246337</td><td>$31,370</td><td>~$32,070</td><td>The Invisible Clarity Tax at maximum. $14,880 over G-VS2 for no visible difference.</td></tr></tbody></table>

*Setting total adds ~$700 for 14k white gold cathedral pavé. Platinum adds $400–$600.

At 2ct, The Invisible Clarity Tax is the primary overspend mechanism. VS1 over VS2 costs $5,970. VVS1 over VS2 costs $14,880. Neither upgrade produces a detectable difference in a round brilliant with a well-cut pavilion. The G-VS2 at $16,490 is unambiguously the correct choice. For a full 2ct buying analysis see the [2 Carat Diamond Engagement Ring guide](https://diamondcritics.com/2-carat-diamond-engagement-ring/).

