## 3 Carat Natural Engagement Rings — What Blue Nile Charges

At 3ct, the engagement ring market enters true luxury territory. A 3ct G-VS2 GIA Excellent round on Blue Nile starts at approximately **$35,000–$40,000** — more than 2× the 2ct price for an 8.9mm stone that measures only 0.8mm wider than the 2ct. The price scaling at 3ct reflects extreme supply rarity: fewer than 1% of all mined diamonds yield a 3ct polished stone.

At this weight, every technical variable matters more than at 1ct or 2ct. The **Bigger Window Effect** becomes relevant — a 3ct table facet is large enough that VS2 inclusions which were invisible at 1ct are potentially detectable at 2× magnification. The audit rule for 3ct natural: always watch the 360° HD video at 10× zoom before purchase. Never buy a 3ct stone on certificate specs alone.

The cut quality requirement also intensifies. A 3ct round brilliant with a depth of 63% or a table of 59% leaks enough light at 8.9mm to be detectable by the naked eye in side-by-side comparison. At 3ct, I recommend tightening the proportion filter to Table 54–56% and Depth 60–62% — one full percentage point narrower than the 1ct filter. For a full 3ct guide with live pricing, see the [3 Carat Diamond Engagement Ring analysis](https://diamondcritics.com/3-carat-diamond-engagement-ring/).

