## Lab Grown Engagement Rings at Blue Nile — The Savings Case

Lab grown diamonds are physically, chemically, and optically identical to natural diamonds. The only difference is origin. Blue Nile carries both IGI and GCAL certified lab diamonds in all major shapes and certifies them transparently alongside natural stones in the same search interface.

The savings at comparable grades are dramatic:

<table class="dc-custom-table"><thead><tr><th>Carat</th><th>Natural Price (G-VS2)</th><th>Lab Price (D-IF)</th><th>Savings</th><th>Lab Stone ID</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>1.5ct</strong></td><td>~$8,500</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29116725?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">$2,930</a></strong></td><td>$5,570 (65%)</td><td>29116725 — IGI Ideal</td></tr><tr><td><strong>2ct</strong></td><td>$16,490</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28629934?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">$2,810</a></strong></td><td>$13,680 (83%)</td><td>28629934 — IGI D-VVS1</td></tr><tr><td><strong>2ct D-IF</strong></td><td>~$25,000+</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28638054?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">$5,780</a></strong></td><td>$19,000+ (76%)</td><td>28638054 — GCAL D-IF Ideal</td></tr><tr><td><strong>3ct D-IF</strong></td><td>~$70,000+</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29116879?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews">$11,770</a></strong></td><td>$58,000+ (83%)</td><td>29116879 — IGI Ideal</td></tr></tbody></table>

The IGI 2ct D-VVS1 lab at **[$2,810](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28629934?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)** is the most powerful value in the entire engagement ring market at any size tier. You are getting D color, VVS1 clarity, 8.1mm face-up for less than most people spend on a natural 1ct stone. The cost: lab diamonds resell at 10–20% of retail versus natural diamonds at 40–50%. If resale matters to you, buy natural. If it doesn't, the $13,680 saved is real money.

The certification rule for lab: IGI, GIA, and GCAL are all acceptable for lab grown diamonds. For natural diamonds, GIA only. Full certification guidance in the [Diamond 4Cs guide](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-4cs/).

