## The Proportion Filter Hack: How to Find the Top 1% of Blue Nile's Inventory

Blue Nile's default search surfaces stones filtered by their recommendation algorithm. This algorithm is designed to present high-margin Astor stones first. To bypass it and access only the best-performing diamonds at any grade, apply these manual filters before anything else:

<table class="dc-custom-table"><thead><tr><th>Filter Parameter</th><th>Target Range</th><th>Why It Matters</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Cut Grade</strong></td><td>Ideal/Excellent only</td><td>Rejects all light-leaking Good and Very Good factory cuts</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Polish & Symmetry</strong></td><td>Excellent only</td><td>Ensures perfect facet alignment and surface finish</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Table %</strong></td><td>54–57%</td><td>Controls the primary light entry window — too wide leaks light</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Depth %</strong></td><td>60–62.5%</td><td>Determines crown-to-pavilion light path — outside range = leakage</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Fluorescence</strong></td><td>None or Faint</td><td>Strong/Medium fluorescence can make stone appear milky in sunlight</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Girdle</strong></td><td>Thin to Slightly Thick</td><td>Very Thick girdles hide weight — stone looks smaller than its carat</td></tr></tbody></table>

Applying all six filters simultaneously reduces a typical 1ct G-VS2 Excellent inventory from 40+ stones to 8–12 stones. Every stone in that filtered set is performing at the top tier of its grade. Every stone you filtered out had a documented optical performance flaw that the Excellent grade label did not catch.

![Blue Nile advanced filter settings hack — Table 54-57% and Depth 60-62.5% manual proportion filter interface showing how to bypass the algorithm's default engagement ring recommendations](/images/blue-nile-advanced-filter-settings-hack-proportions.avif "Blue Nile Engagement Ring Filter Hack: Proportion Parameters That Bypass the Algorithm")

