## Build Your Own Ring: How the Process Actually Works

Blue Nile's [Build Your Own Ring](https://www.bluenile.com/build-your-own-ring?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) is a three-step process:

**Step 1 — Select your diamond.** Apply the proportion filters above. Pick the stone that passes the proportion check, shows a clean 360° video, has no fluorescence issues, and falls at the grade sweet spot for your budget. Note the GIA report number.

**Step 2 — Select your setting.** Choose style (solitaire, pavé, cathedral, three-stone), metal (14k white/yellow/rose gold, 18k, platinum), and prong count. Confirm the setting is compatible with your diamond's shape — Blue Nile's system will flag incompatibilities automatically.

**Step 3 — Confirm and order.** At checkout, Blue Nile shows the combined price, estimated setting time (typically 7–12 business days), and shipping date. For proposals, order at minimum 3 weeks before your target date. Custom settings in designer lines (Monique Lhuillier, Zac Posen) require 4–6 weeks.

One important note from my customer experience research: Blue Nile's 30-day return window runs from the delivery date, not the order date. For custom-set engagement rings, the clock starts when you receive the finished ring. Keep the original packaging, GIA certificate, and all documentation — Blue Nile's return process is frictionless if you have all three. Missing any one of them creates friction.

