## Frequently Asked Questions

### Is Blue Nile a good place to buy an engagement ring?

Yes — for buyers who can apply manual proportion filters and verify GIA report data. Blue Nile offers the world's largest GIA-certified inventory, full price transparency, and competitive pricing that is typically 20–40% below equivalent quality at local jewelers. The risk is the default algorithm, which surfaces high-margin stones. Apply the Table 54–57% and Depth 60–62.5% filters before evaluating any stone.

### What is the cheapest engagement ring at Blue Nile?

The least expensive GIA-certified engagement ring (loose diamond + solitaire setting) starts at approximately $800–$1,200 for a 0.3–0.5ct G-VS2 round in 14k white gold. For buyers targeting 1ct — the most common benchmark — the floor is $3,230 for the loose stone plus $470 for a solitaire setting, totaling approximately $3,700 as a complete ring.

### Does Blue Nile negotiate on engagement ring prices?

Blue Nile does not negotiate in the traditional sense, but they offer a price match guarantee. If you find the exact GIA certificate number listed for less at a competitor (including James Allen), present the competitor price and Blue Nile will typically match it to secure your purchase.

### How long does Blue Nile take to make an engagement ring?

Standard solitaire settings ship in 7–10 business days after diamond selection. Pavé and more complex settings take 10–14 business days. Designer collection settings (Monique Lhuillier, Zac Posen) require 4–6 weeks. For proposals with a fixed date, always add one week buffer to the quoted timeline and order accordingly.

### What is the Astor by Blue Nile diamond?

Astor is Blue Nile's in-house branded super-ideal cut diamond. Every Astor stone carries both a GIA certificate and a GCAL light performance certificate. The premium over a standard GIA Excellent diamond at identical specs is typically 15–25%. In my testing, standard GIA Excellent diamonds with correct proportions (Table 54–57%, Depth 60–62.5%) perform identically to Astor stones in real-world lighting. For most buyers, Astor is a $500–$2,000 premium for a second certificate on top of an already-excellent-performing stone.

### Can I return an engagement ring to Blue Nile?

Yes. Blue Nile offers a 30-day return window from the delivery date on all engagement ring purchases, including custom-set rings. Requirements: original packaging, GIA certificate, and any documentation received with the order. Missing documentation creates friction in the return process. Keep everything.

